    <h1>Chua Swee Ann</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201109/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-09"><time>2020-11-09</time></a>
        - <span>PLACE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>man­ag­ing direc­tor and chief ex­ec­u­tive of­fi­cer, Bintai Kindenko</p>
    <p>On hav­ing a safety mind­set…</p>
    <p>“It’s all about tak­ing the time to take care of our­selves and those around us ev­ery day on the job. It’s about our com­mu­nity and our col­lec­tive well-be­ing. We must all be pas­sion­ate about safety, and con­stantly re­in­force it within our col­lec­tive con­scious­ness. It’s one thing to say ‘safety mat­ters’, but an­other to have it in­deli­bly etched into the minds of the work­force.</p>
    <p>“We stay safe to­gether. Safety as a way of life is a cul­tural mind­set that can be in­grained and built upon over the years”.</p>
    <p>On giv­ing em­ploy­ees a voice and own­er­ship in the com­pany’s suc­cesses...</p>
    <p>“Our em­ploy­ees and sub­con­trac­tors are our great­est as­set. It is only through them that we can achieve suc­cess. There­fore, we do all that we can to pro­tect them from in­juries and ill­nesses.”</p>
    <p>On em­pow­er­ing em­ploy­ees and staff…</p>
    <p>“We en­cour­age them to con­duct risk eval­u­a­tions and iden­tify haz­ards and stop any un­safe works. Our ‘Own­er­ship Think­ing’ process teaches em­ploy­ees to think like an owner, and to ex­press their ideas and thoughts on how to make Bintai Kindenko a bet­ter, safer and health­ier com­pany.</p>
    <p>“Since the in­cep­tion of ‘Own­er­ship Think­ing’, over 17 new ideas on dig­i­tal ini­tia­tives or pro­grammes have been pro­posed by com­pany em­ploy­ees.”</p>


